Key Match Events: Shaheen Afridi was too greedy, and smoked one straight to Marnus Labuschagne on the square leg boundary.
Zampa has his second successive four-wicket haul, he's lured Mohammad Nawaz out of his crease.
Rizwan is now gone! Is that all she wrote for Pakistan?
Iftikhar Ahmed has arrived at the crease with a licence to swing apparently. He's dispatched Pat Cummins over the fence twice, and has now taken it to Marcus Stoinis as well.
Pre-Game Insights: David Warner has downplayed concerns he's carrying a groin injury, despite spending a majority of the Pakistan innings in the pavilion.
Post-Match Reflections: Mark Taylor believes Australia are 'finding their groove' after claiming their second win of the World Cup.
Warner scored a sensational 163 for man of the match honours, but disappeared from the ground early on in Pakistan's reply.
With the ball, Hazlewood was fantastic, as was Zampa.
Fielding was good without being great - a couple of dropped catches, but if we get that right, I think we are back into the tournament.
